</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperMonitoring&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperMonitoring&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Systems that run Docker and Kubernetes can be monitored in various ways.
</p><p>Docker provides basic runtime metrics through the use of “docker stats”.
</p><p>See <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/admin/runmetrics/">https://docs.docker.com/engine/admin/runmetrics/</a>.
</p><p>In the CDF, monitoring occurs at the Kubernetes level.
</p><p>The monitoring data is collected from Docker by cAdvisor which acts as an abstraction layer for particular container runtime engines.
</p><p>The CDF includes Heapster and Metrics Server for cluster-wide monitoring. Both talk directly to Kubernetes metrics endpoints where the raw data is provided by the Kubelet.
</p><p>The Kubelet gets this information from cAdvisor.
</p><p>The Kubelet information is then aggregated by Heapster/Metrics Server and visualized via the Kubernetes dashboard.
</p><p>See <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/resource-usage-monitoring/">https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/resource-usage-monitoring/</a>&nbsp;; <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://github.com/kubernetes/heapster">https://github.com/kubernetes/heapster</a>&nbsp;; <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/resource-metrics-pipeline/">https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/resource-metrics-pipeline/</a>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Additional_CDF_manageability">Additional CDF manageability</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperMonitoring&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperMonitoring&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-2" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Through the <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://marketplace.microfocus.com/itom/category/cdf">Micro Focus marketplace for CDF</a>, additional monitoring packages from our Micro Focus partners are available for download.
</p>
